OL,3,CHospital porters to strike over
OL,4,C'bullying and harassment'
OL,6,FKate Attwooll, Regional Officer, Unite
OL,7,Fthe Union, said: "The strike action
OL,8,Fwill inevitably cause serious
OL,9,Fdisruption across the hospital but
OL,10,Fthis is entirely the fault of
OL,11,Fmanagement, they are well aware of the
OL,12,Fproblems but have failed to take
OL,13,Faction to prioritise staff and patient
OL,14,Fsafety and dignity.
OL,16,F"Strike action could still be avoided
OL,17,Fbut that would require management
OL,18,Fintroducing the changes needed to end
OL,19,Fthe endemic bullying of porters at
OL,20,FUHS."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
